The article is a White House briefing by Press Secretary Robert Gibbs. Gibbs discusses President Obama's meeting with Senate Democrats to discuss healthcare reform. The President expressed the importance of getting healthcare reform done and went through the key points of the bill. He also expressed optimism that they were closer than ever to getting it done. Gibbs also discusses the progress made in closing Guantanamo Bay and the purchase of the Thomson facility in Illinois. He addresses concerns about security and cost, and emphasizes that closing Guantanamo Bay will make the country safer. Gibbs also talks about the President's conversations with world leaders regarding climate change negotiations in Copenhagen. He mentions progress in the START negotiations but says there are no plans for a signing ceremony in Copenhagen. Finally, Gibbs mentions that the President believes the healthcare bill contains important reforms and urges members of both sides of the Democratic Caucus to support it.